rComments: Restored my love of studio classes

Won't tell you what he wants to see in an assignment, will give you guidelines that are not enforced. If you ask him a question, you will get a deeply philosophical metaphor designed to broaden your thinking. That said, he is a wonderful instructor and very good at aiding the creative process

Fantastic instructor. Lectures are interesting and the assignments are reasonably marked. Boigon links philosophy to architecture in today's complex urban environment. I would strongly advise taking his courses if you want to be mentally challenged.

Most entertaining lectures. He definitely broadened our definition of architecture and had a lot to say about popular culture. He's really enthusiastic about what he's teaching, but some of us just question the relevance sometimes.
